### Description

Third party that I'm using provide css files with .module.css extension . I'm registering in `angular.json >project > angular-app > architect > build > options > styles `these files as styles to be imported directly in the global so I can consume them in the application without any suffixes and prefixes:
```json
{
  ....
      "architect": {
        "build": {
          "options": {
            "styles": [
              "src/styles.css",
              "thirparty_module/ExternalStyles.module.css",
            ],
  ....
```

Then I'm adding these imports in `src/styles.css` using `@use`

```css
/* You can add global styles to this file, and also import other style files */
@use '@ui5/webcomponents/dist/styles/Input.module.css';
```

But when I inspect the inject style element the styles look:
```css
/* src/styles.css */
@use "thirparty_module/ExternalStyles.module.css";

/* ../thirparty_module/ExternalStyles.module.css */
.Input_inputIcon {
```

Is it expected these modules to be processed because I read that these files are no longer processed due to webpack specific requirements?

